  "text": "Our plate tectonic reconstructions of the South American margin and potential conjugate bathymetric anomalies when paired with the history of flat slabs compiled by [CITATION_1] shows that there is no clear link between a subducting anomaly and zones of flat subduction. We have shown previously that the correlation between current flat slabs and subducting crustal anomalies does not exist and therefore buoyant bathymetric anomalies cannot be the sole cause of flat slabs. With this series of reconstructions we have shown that the correlation between bathymetric anomalies and flat slabs did not exist in the past and that the Inca Plateau was mislocated.",
